<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Actually Ghosh states in an interview that the story for Neel Rattan Halder came from his research. He stumbled upon mention of a zemindar named Pran <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Actually Ghosh states in an interview that the story for Neel Rattan Halder came from his research. He stumbled upon mention of a zemindar named Pran Krishna Halder, spelled as "Prawn Kissin Halder" who was tried for forgery. This is where Neel's story comes from. The Q&amp;A notes can be found here: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/review-book-review-flood-of-fire-2093091">http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/rev...</a><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
