<div id="review_2516202542" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2516202542" />
    <a title="Ann-Marie &quot;Cookie M.&quot;" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58567012-ann-marie-cookie-m"><img alt="Ann-Marie &quot;Cookie M.&quot;" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607273374p2/58567012.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2516202542?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ann-Marie &quot;Cookie M.&quot;" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ann-Marie &quot;Cookie M.&quot;" href="/user/show/58567012-ann-marie-cookie-m">Ann-Marie &quot;Cookie M.&quot;</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8123911-sea-of-poppies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2516202542" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7383345054888470632">&quot;Sea of Poppies&quot; introduced a world I did not really know existed, a world where British people reduced and degraded an entire continent of people in their greed.<br/> This is the story of several of those people, some of them connected tangentially, some of them not at all who end up together struggling for life and dignity aboard the ship Ibis in the Bay of Bengal.<br/> I was so caught up in the story I was not ready for it to end. Good thing it is part of a trilogy.</span>
  <span id="freeText7383345054888470632" style="display:none">"Sea of Poppies" introduced a world I did not really know existed, a world where British people reduced and degraded an entire continent of people in their greed.<br /> This is the story of several of those people, some of them connected tangentially, some of them not at all who end up together struggling for life and dignity aboard the ship Ibis in the Bay of Bengal.<br /> I was so caught up in the story I was not ready for it to end. Good thing it is part of a trilogy.</span>
