<div id="review_1519785068" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1519785068" />
    <a title="Joshua Rigsby" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12022033-joshua-rigsby"><img alt="Joshua Rigsby" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1355723807p2/12022033.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1519785068?book_show_action=true">Jan 21, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joshua Rigsby" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joshua Rigsby" href="/user/show/12022033-joshua-rigsby">Joshua Rigsby</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780374174224" href="/book/show/3619371-sea-of-poppies">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12022033-joshua-rigsby?shelf=literary">literary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12022033-joshua-rigsby?shelf=for-fun-modern">for-fun-modern</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12022033-joshua-rigsby?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/12022033-joshua-rigsby?shelf=nautical">nautical</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1519785068" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1192062009994530758">A wonderful book. Ghosh&apos;s attention to character and affection for language brim to the top of every page. It was wonderful to see the opium trade from a multiplicity of perspectives, classes, idioms, and ethnicities. He does get a little too specific with his jargon at times, leaving the reader to grope around the context for possible meanings, but this is my only minor qualm. I&apos;d recommend this book to anyone. <br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://joshuarigsby.com'>http://joshuarigsby.com</a></span>
  <span id="freeText1192062009994530758" style="display:none">A wonderful book. Ghosh's attention to character and affection for language brim to the top of every page. It was wonderful to see the opium trade from a multiplicity of perspectives, classes, idioms, and ethnicities. He does get a little too specific with his jargon at times, leaving the reader to grope around the context for possible meanings, but this is my only minor qualm. I'd recommend this book to anyone. <br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://joshuarigsby.com">http://joshuarigsby.com</a></span>
